# Security Operations — Cursor AI Context (POC)

## Environment
- SIEM: Microsoft Sentinel (target — not yet connected in POC)
- Cloud platforms: AWS (primary), Azure (target — not yet connected in POC)
- Identity: Microsoft Entra ID
- EDR: Microsoft Defender for Endpoint
- E5 licence in use: Defender XDR, Purview, MDA

## POC Approach
- All tools run locally using flat files and public APIs only
- No Azure SDK, no AWS SDK, no live Sentinel connection in this phase
- Local KQL rule files use YAML frontmatter for metadata (name, severity, tactics, techniques)
- Live connections will be added later — code should be structured so they are easy to swap in

## Python Conventions
- Python 3.12
- Use pip and virtual environments (venv) for dependency management
- All secrets via environment variables loaded from a .env file using python-dotenv
- Never hardcode secrets, API keys, or URLs
- Use pytest for all tests, mock all HTTP calls and file I/O
- Use the `rich` library for any terminal output that should be formatted nicely
- Structure code so external API calls are isolated in their own modules — easy to swap later
- LLM access goes through `shared/llm.py` (`complete()`); add providers there rather than in tools

## KQL Rule File Format (local POC)
- Files saved as .kql with YAML frontmatter between --- markers
- Frontmatter fields: name, description, severity, enabled, tactics (list), techniques (list),
  entity_mappings (list)
- Example:
  ---
  name: [MITRE TACTIC] Suspicious Sign-in from Tor Exit Node
  description: Detects sign-ins originating from known Tor exit nodes
  severity: High
  enabled: true
  tactics:
    - InitialAccess
  techniques:
    - T1078
  entity_mappings:
    - Account
    - IPAddress
  ---
  // KQL rule body here

## ATT&CK
- Use mitreattack-python library for all MITRE data
- Always reference Enterprise ATT&CK matrix (not Mobile or ICS)
- Technique ID format: T1078 (not T1078.004 unless sub-technique is specifically needed)

## Project Structure
- Each tool lives in its own subdirectory
- Shared utilities go in /shared/
- All secrets in .env file — never committed to Git
- Output files go in each tool's /output/ directory
- Sample/test data goes in each tool's /sample_data/ directory